21/08/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A parliamentary commission investigating alleged misappropriation by former Parliament Speaker Zlatko Tomcic and former Construction Minister Radimir Cacic will be completed soon, panel chairman Nenad Stazic said Friday (19 August). Tomcic, who also leads the Croatian Farmers Party, and Cacic are being investigated for alleged irregularities and conflict of interest in relation to state orders issued by the Construction Ministry to a local firm, Capital Ing, in 2000-2003. According to reports, Tomcic held a 22 per cent stake in the company, which was granted some contracts without the required consent of the government public procurement office. (HINA, index.hr - 19/08/05)
